Wayne Rooney has admitted he watched Manchester United's latest superstar signing Radamel Falcao in action on YouTube before his deadline day move to Old Trafford.

The Manchester United captain is a keen admirer of the Colombian forward and said he used the global video-sharing website to see a collection of the 28-year-old's career goals.

He told the Sunday Mirror: 'Yes, I've YouTubed his goals of course. But I have seen him play throughout the years for Atletico Madrid. It is exciting for us at United and also for the Premier League that he has signed.

