'Falcao is a world-class player and one who could have gone to a number of other clubs so it's great we've got him.

'I just hope he hasn't picked up any little injuries while he has been away with Colombia. It's a great signing but it's also a great ­statement of intent from the club.' 

Rooney conceded that while last season was unacceptable he remains hopeful the glory days will now return to Old Trafford sooner rather than later. 

