He added: 'Obviously last season, we all know we were not good enough. But the time is now right to get these top players to get us back to where we belong – winning titles again.'

The Red Devils take on newly-promoted QPR at Old Trafford on Sunday afternoon as they look for their first league win of the season, which could see Falcao, as well as Daley Blind, Marcos Rojo and Luke  Shaw handed their United debuts by Louis van Gaal.

